msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1493
msgid "Package Policy"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1495
msgid ""
"Before sending your recipe to upstream (to become a public package), you "
"must follow these rules:"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1497
msgid "Naming"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1499
msgid "The recipe name can't have dots, backslashes, and NULs"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1501
msgid "Cross-Compilation"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1503
msgid ""
"All recipes must use our cross-compilers, a Cookbook [template](#templates) "
"does this automatically but it's not always possible, study the build system "
"of your application or library to find these options or patch the "
"configuration files."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1504
msgid ""
"Don't hardcode the CPU architecture on the recipe script (this would break "
"the multi-arch support)."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1508
msgid ""
"Don't use the auto-generated tarballs from GitHub, they aren't static and "
"don't verify the archive integrity."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1510
msgid "API Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1512
msgid ""
"Respect the API compatibility of C/C++ libraries, for example: if `openssl1` "
"is available and some application need `openssl3`, you will create a recipe "
"for `openssl3` and not rename the `openssl1`, as it will break the dependent "
"packages."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1514
msgid ""
"(Read [this](./developer-faq.md#why-cc-applications-and-libraries-are-hard-"
"and-time-consuming-to-port) section to know why it's needed)"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1516
msgid "Checksum"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1518
msgid ""
"If your recipe download a tarball, you will need to create a BLAKE3 hash for "
"it. You can learn how to do it [here](#create-a-blake3-hash-for-your-recipe)."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1520
msgid "License"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1522
msgid "Don't package applications or libraries lacking a license."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1523
msgid ""
"Verify if the application has some license violation, in case of doubt ask "
"us on the [chat](https://doc.redox-os.org/book/chat.html)."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1524
msgid ""
"Non-free applications and assets should go to a subcategory of the `nonfree` "
"category and be approved per license."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1526
msgid "Testing Area"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1528
msgid ""
"Work-in-progress software ports goes to the `wip` category, be aware of "
"these items during your packaging process:"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1530
msgid "A recipe is considered ready if it's mostly working inside of Redox."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1531
msgid ""
"All WIP recipes must have a `#TODO` on the beginning of the `recipe.toml` "
"and explain what is missing."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1532
msgid "BLAKE3 hashes for tarballs are optional (quick testing workflow)"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1533
msgid ""
"Try to keep the recipe with the latest stable version of the application "
"(the porting process can take months)."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1534
msgid ""
"Once the recipe is ready, add the BLAKE3 hash if needed and move the folder "
"to the appropriate category."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1536
msgid "Suggestions for TODOs"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1538
msgid "These TODOs improve the packagers cooperation and understanding."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1540
msgid ""
"`not compiled or tested` - It means that your recipe may be fully or "
"partially configured and with necessary dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1541
msgid ""
"`missing script for x: insert-the-link-for-build-instructions-here` - It "
"means that your recipe is lacking the cross-compilation script for some "
"build system, where `x` is the build system name. After `:` you will insert "
"the link for the build instructions of the application or library, it will "
"help other packagers to create the script for you."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1542
msgid ""
"`missing dependencies: insert-the-link-for-required-dependencies-here` - It "
"means that the `build.dependencies` or `package.dependencies` data types are "
"incomplete."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1543
msgid ""
"`probably wrong script: insert-the-link-for-build-instructions-here` - It "
"means that you don't know yet if your script is working."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1544
msgid ""
"`probably wrong template: insert-the-link-for-build-instructions-here` - It "
"means that you don't know yet if the Cookbook template is working."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1545
msgid ""
"`probably missing dependencies: insert-the-link-for-required-dependencies-"
"here` - It means that you don't know yet if the required dependencies are "
"satisfied."
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1546
msgid ""
"`promote` - It means that the recipe is working and should be moved to the "
"equivalent category at `recipes/*`"
msgstr ""

#: src/porting-applications.md:1548
msgid "Other TODOs are specific and won't be covered on this list."
msgstr ""
